    "created_at": "2014-08-01T17:52:51Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-08-01T17:52:51Z",
    "body": "I do feel a little uncomfortable about the timer API being coupled to channels, but I'm thinking we can let stability attributes deal with this, and if the 1.0 timer API isn't the best it's not the end of the world.\n\nThe biggest concern with leaving them together is that it makes refactoring channels and I/O into different crates difficult or impossible.\n\nNominating for removal from milestone.\n",
