    "created_at": "2015-03-11T00:21:23Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-03-11T00:21:23Z",
    "body": "Channel based timers are part of `old_io` and are not coming back as part of the new I/O. I've opened [an RFC issue](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/issues/962) for adding `recv_timeout` which is useful no matter what. In light of channel-based timers not coming back, though, I'm going to close this in favor of the RFC issue as it will be a backwards compatible addition.\n",
